'''Alessandro Circati''' ({{IPA|it|alesˈsandro tʃirˈkaːti|lang}}; born 10 October 2003) is a professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[central defender]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|alessandro-circati/643874}}</ref> Born in Italy and a former youth international for Italy, he plays for and has [[Captain (association football)|captain]]ed the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]]. Long regarded as one of the best young talents in Australian soccer, he is considered as one of the best Australian players of his generation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://football360.com.au/socceroos-news-alessandro-circati-captains-parma-serie-a-fiorentina-details-reaction/|title=Socceroos star Circati's incredible return: Aussie becomes a Serie A captain at 22|first=Jake|last=Rosengarten|publisher=[[Football360]]|date=28 December 2025}}</ref>

==Early life==
Circati was born in [[Fidenza]], Italy, to [[Gianfranco Circati]], who was a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kick360.co/parmas-alessandro-circati-on-great-honour-of-italy-and-australia-call-ups-and-playing-with-gianluigi-buffon/|title=Parma's Alessandro Circati on "great honour" of Italy and Australia call-ups and playing with Gianluigi Buffon|website=kick360.com.au|date=21 April 2022 }}</ref> Born in the [[province of Parma]] and [[Emilia-Romagna]] region of Italy, his grandparents resided in [[Salsomaggiore Terme]] and originated from the region.<ref name="sbsitaliano"/> Circati moved to [[Perth]], Australia at the age of one.<ref name="sbssport">{{cite web |last1=Davidson |first1=John |title=Aussie defender Circati following in footsteps of Socceroos greats |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/sport/article/aussie-defender-circati-following-in-footsteps-of-socceroos-greats/od0y763ox |website=SBS Sport |language=en |date=10 March 2021}}</ref> As a youth during school, Circati played football and [[Australian rules football]], although focussed more on the former as he was "okay" at Aussie rules.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Peacock |first1=Adam |title=Newest Socceroo Alessandro Circati explains why he chose Australia over Italy before Argentina match |url=https://www.codesports.com.au/football/newest-socceroo-alessandro-circati-explains-why-he-australia-over-italy-before-argentina-match/news-story/3ebb8879c2c24f3879ebb3f7d3f88f66 |website=Code Sports |access-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230613215906/https://www.codesports.com.au/football/newest-socceroo-alessandro-circati-explains-why-he-australia-over-italy-before-argentina-match/news-story/3ebb8879c2c24f3879ebb3f7d3f88f66 |url-access=subscription |archive-date=13 June 2023 |date=14 June 2023}}</ref> He attended [[Servite College]] during high school and idolised [[Paolo Maldini]].<ref name="servite">{{cite web |title=Servite College {{!}} Perseverance and Resilience |url=https://www.servite.wa.edu.au/community-atributes/ |website=Servite |publisher=iServi News |date=30 August 2019}}</ref> Circati began his football career at [[Perth SC]] until the age of 14 when he moved to the [[Perth Glory FC Youth|academy system]] of [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]].<ref name="keepup-pg">{{cite web |title=PGFC Academy starlet snapped up Serie A club |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/pgfc-academy-starlet-snapped-serie-a-club |website=KEEPUP |publisher=[[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]] |date=10 March 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Alessandro Circati is Parma's next great Aussie hope |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2021/12/02/alessandro-circati-is-parmas-next-great-aussie-hope/ |website=The Roar |date=1 December 2021}}</ref>

== Club career ==
===Perth Glory===
Circati played for Perth Glory in the [[National Premier Leagues]] (NPL) youth competitions in [[National Premier Leagues Western Australia|Western Australia]].<ref name="keepup-pg"/> Since joining in 2017, he was part of the under-20s team that claimed the league title and the State League Reserves Cup in the 2019 season, winning the cup final against [[Cockburn City SC|Cockburn City]] at [[Dorrien Gardens]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Murray hat-trick steers Academy Under-20s to Cup glory |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/murray-hat-trick-steers-academy-under-20s-cup-glory |website=KEEPUP |publisher=Perth Glory |date=22 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Academy First Team taste defeat, but joy for U-18s and U-20s |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/academy-first-team-taste-defeat-joy-u-18s-and-u-20s |website=KEEPUP |publisher=Perth Glory |date=1 September 2019}}</ref>

Circati played for the NPL senior squad mid-season of 2019 and scored his first senior goal against [[Sorrento FC]] on 15 July 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Glory edged out by Gulls |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/glory-edged-out-gulls |website=KEEPUP |publisher=Perth Glory |date=15 July 2019}}</ref> He also played in the [[A-League Youth]] competition for Perth Glory although his side finished last by the end of the campaign with no wins.<ref>{{cite web |title=Glory edged out in final game of season |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/glory-edged-out-final-game-season |website=KEEPUP |publisher=Perth Glory |date=27 January 2020}}</ref> By the end of the [[2020 National Premier Leagues|2020 season]], Circati received Most Glorious Youth Player Award by Perth Glory at the club's award ceremony, recognising his performances whilst playing with the academy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fornaroli, Kilkenny and Celia claim 2019/20 MGP honours |url=https://perthglory.com.au/news/fornaroli-kilkenny-and-celia-claim-201920-mgp-honours |website=KEEPUP |publisher=Perth Glory |date=10 November 2020}}</ref>

===Parma===
Circati underwent trials with several European clubs, including [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester]] and [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] in England, where he spent three months before having to move on due to the complications brought about by [[Brexit]].<ref name="sbssport"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Abbott |first1=Matt |title=Former Leicester trialist Circati explains reason behind Serie B switch |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/leicester-city-trialist-reading-parma-6859484 |website=LeicestershireLive |language=en |date=25 March 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Parma, Circati: "Stiamo cercando di riportare il club dove merita, in Serie A" |url=https://www.ilovepalermocalcio.com/parma-circati-stiamo-cercando-di-riportare-il-club-dove-merita-in-serie-a/ |website=I love Palermo Calcio |access-date=12 February 2024 |language=it-IT |date=29 November 2023}}</ref> According to reports, Leicester were considering making an offer to the young player, but due to his Italian passport and young age, finalising a deal proved to be difficult.<ref name="sbsitaliano">{{cite web |last1=Oreglia |first1=Carlo |title=Di padre in figlio: l'italo-australiano Alessandro Circati a Parma 25 anni dopo il padre Gianfranco |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/language/italian/it/podcast-episode/di-padre-in-figlio-litalo-australiano-alessandro-circati-a-parma-25-anni-dopo-il-padre-gianfranco/7xz2kye07 |website=SBS Language |language=it |date=29 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Coast |first1=Tom |title=Player chose another club over Leicester 'to go and live with grandparents' – 'Returning home' |url=https://sportwitness.co.uk/player-chose-another-club-leicester/ |website=Sport Witness |date=24 March 2022}}</ref> Influenced from his father and the connection to his hometown, Circati joined Parma on 10 March 2021 after a successful trial period with the club.<ref name="keepup-pg"/><ref>{{cite web |last1=Manara |first1=Fabio |title=Circati: "Papà Gianfranco un bravo allenatore. Felice di essere a Parma" |url=https://www.forzaparma.it/2021/03/03/circati-papa-gianfranco-un-bravo-allenatore-felice-di-essere-a-parma/ |website=Forza Parma |language=it-IT |date=3 March 2021}}</ref> On 10 January 2022, Circati was announced to have signed his first professional contract, a two-year contract expiring in 2024, with Parma.<ref>{{cite web |title=CIRCATI AND AWUA SIGN FIRST PRO DEALS |url=https://parmacalcio1913.com/2022/01/10/circati-and-awua-sign-first-pro-deals/?lang=en |website=[[Parma Calcio 1913]] |date=10 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Perth teen is Parma's next Aussie hope |url=https://thewest.com.au/sport/perth-glory/perth-glory-academy-product-alessandro-circati-signs-two-year-deal-with-italian-serie-b-club-parma--c-5266284 |website=The West Australian |language=en |date=12 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Paquette |first1=Catherine |title=Former A-League Youth Perth starlet signs with Italian Serie B giants |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/former-a-league-youth-perth-starlet-signs-with-italian-serie-b-giants-574524 |website=FTBL |date=11 January 2022}}</ref>

Displaying consistent performances in the youth sector,<ref>{{cite web |title=Alessandro Circati, la giovane speranza del Parma |url=https://www.legab.it/news/alessandro-circati-la-giovane-speranza-del-parma |website=Liga B |publisher=BKT Series |language=it |date=30 August 2022}}</ref> Circati was promoted to train with the first team, sharing a dressing room with experienced Italian international [[Gianluigi Buffon]], who served as a mentor to him when he first joined the club.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rugari |first1=Vince |title=Socceroos make pitch for young Italian star being nurtured by Buffon |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/socceroos-make-pitch-for-young-italian-star-being-nurtured-by-buffon-20221010-p5boin.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |language=en |date=10 October 2022}}</ref> On 26 February 2022, Circati made his professional debut for Parma, starting and keeping a clean sheet in a 4–0 win against [[S.P.A.L.|SPAL]] in [[Serie B]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Alessandro Circati dopo Parma-Spal: 'Una Bella Emozione, ringrazio il Mister E I Miei Compagni' |url=https://parmacalcio1913.com/2022/02/26/alessandro-circati-dopo-parma-spal-una-bella-emozione-ringrazio-il-mister-e-i-miei-compagni/ |website=Parma Calcio 1913 |language=it-IT |date=26 February 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Perth graduate's Italian breakthrough comes with Buffon's backing |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/perth-teen-has-serie-b-moment-with-buffons-backing/ |website=KEEPUP |language=en-AU |date=2 March 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title="It Was My Moment": Circati Relishes Italian Football Debut |url=https://davidferrini.substack.com/p/it-was-my-moment-circati-relishes |website=David Ferrini |publisher=Lega Football |language=en |date=28 February 2022}}</ref> In the [[2021–22 Serie B|2021–22 season]], he made a total of 6 league appearances and 2 assists in the games against [[Cosenza Calcio|Cosenza]] and [[U.S. Alessandria Calcio 1912|Alessandria]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farina |first1=Michele |title=La famiglia nel pallone: Gianfranco e Alessandro Circati |url=https://11contro11.it/la-famiglia-nel-pallone-gianfranco-e-alessandro-circati/ |website=11contro11 |language=it-IT |date=23 December 2022}}</ref> On 8 June, Circati renewed his contract with Parma, tying him with the club until the end of the 2026–27 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=ALESSANDRO CIRCATI RINNOVA FINO AL 2027: AVANTI INSIEME! |url=https://parmacalcio1913.com/2023/06/08/alessandro-circati-rinnova-fino-al-2027-avanti-insieme/ |website=Parma Calcio 1913 |language=it-IT |date=8 June 2023}}</ref> In the [[2022–23 Parma Calcio 1913 season|2022–23 season]], Circati made 17 appearances for Parma across all competitions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alessandro Circati signs extension with Parma until 2027 |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/alessandro-circati-signs-extension-parma-until-2027 |website=Socceroos |language=en |date=9 June 2023}}</ref>

Circati scored his first professional goal on 24 September 2023 in a 1–1 draw to [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], extending Parma's 16-game unbeaten streak during the [[2023–24 Serie B|2023–24 Serie B season]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ferrini |first1=David |title='A Dream Come True': Circati on Goalscoring Milestone For Parma |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidferrini/2023/09/28/a-dream-come-true-circati-on-goalscoring-milestone-for-parma/?sh=60f393027ecd |website=Forbes |access-date=15 October 2023 |language=en |date=28 September 2023}}</ref> In [[2023–24 Parma Calcio 1913 season|that season]], Parma earned promotion to [[Serie A]], the first time since the [[2020–21 Parma Calcio 1913 season|2020–21 season]], and progressed to the [[2023–24 Coppa Italia|Round of 16]] in the [[Coppa Italia]]. Circati made 32 appearances and one goal across all competitions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alessandro Circati secures Serie A promotion with Parma |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/alessandro-circati-secures-serie-a-promotion-parma |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=19 June 2024 |language=en |date=2 May 2024}}</ref>

== International career ==
=== Italy ===
Circati, being of dual [[Australians|Australian]] and [[Italians|Italian]] nationality, received offers from both countries to represent them in international football.<ref>{{cite web |title=L'Australia pensa a Circati |url=https://www.forzaparma.it/2022/09/07/laustralia-pensa-a-circati/ |website=Forza Parma |language=it-IT |date=7 September 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Troop |first1=Guglielmo |title=L'Italia guarda il Parma, Nicolato: "Seguiamo anche Circati" |url=https://www.parmatoday.it/sport/l-italia-guarda-il-parma-nicolato-seguiamo-anche-circati.html |website=ParmaToday |language=it |date=10 March 2023}}</ref> In March 2022, Circati was selected by [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20]] for two friendly matches against [[Germany national under-20 football team|Germany]] and [[Norway national under-20 football team|Norway]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Buratti |first1=Simone |title=Otto crociati in Nazionale: debutto assoluto per Circati con l'Italia U20 |url=https://www.ilparmense.net/otto-crociati-in-nazionale/ |website=ilParmense.net |language=it-IT |date=22 March 2022}}</ref> On 28 March, he made his debut against Norway as a starter and helped keep a clean sheet in a 5–0 win for the Azzurri.<ref>{{cite web |title=Italia U20, buon debutto per Circati: gli azzurrini strapazzano la Norvegia |url=https://www.parmalive.com/news/italia-u20-buon-debutto-per-circati-gli-azzurrini-strapazzano-la-norvegia-191987 |website=Parma Live |language=it}}</ref> In September 2022, he was called up to the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]] alongside Australian-born player [[Cristian Volpato]].<ref>{{cite web |title=CROCIATI NATIONAL CALL-UPS – FIRST CALL-UP FOR ALESSANDRO CIRCATI WITH ITALY UNDER 21s |url=https://parmacalcio1913.com/2022/09/19/crociati-national-call-ups-first-call-up-for-alessandro-circati-with-italy-under-21s/?lang=en |website=Parma Calcio 1913 |date=19 September 2022}}</ref> He was an unused substitute in the friendly against [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]] on 26 September 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=国際親善試合 日程・結果 |url=http://jfa.jp/national_team/u21_2022/20220922/match_page/m2.html |website=JFA｜公益財団法人日本サッカー協会 |language=ja |date=26 September 2022}}</ref>

===Australia===
On 6 June 2023, after talks with [[Graham Arnold]] and a phone call with his family, Circati made the decision to represent [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] rather than Italy, rejecting the ''Gli Azzurrini'' call-up to their youth team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Socceroo set for dramatic 18-year first in Serie A thanks to Paulo Dybala & a new rule |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/keepup-beyond-the-a-leagues-socceroo-set-for-18-year-serie-a-first-after-90th-minute-lifeline/ |website=KEEPUP |access-date=6 June 2023 |language=en-AU |date=5 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Arnold buoyed as Circati rejects Italy for Socceroos |url=https://www.riverineherald.com.au/aap-soccer/arnold-buoyed-as-circati-rejects-italy-for-socceroos/ |website=Riverine Herald |access-date=6 June 2023 |date=6 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Brunsdon |first1=Simon |title=Gun Italian teen pledges allegiance to Socceroos |url=https://wwos.nine.com.au/football/news-2023-socceroos-squad-vs-argentina-alessandro-circati-graham-arnold-coach/7cc4ec66-3c48-4154-9a1f-825e93389cbf |website=wwos.nine.com.au |access-date=6 June 2023 |language=en |date=6 June 2023}}</ref> He was added to the 23-man squad set to play against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in [[Beijing]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Parma defender Alessandro Circati named in Socceroos squad for Argentina clash |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-06-06/alessandro-circati-named-in-australian-squad/102447240 |publisher=ABC News|location=Australia |language=en-AU |date=6 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Thomas |first1=Joshua |title=Socceroos name Italy youth international Alessandro Circati in squad to take on Argentina |url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/socceroos/os58520/socceroos-argentina-squad-alessandro-circati-italy |website=Optus Sport |access-date=6 June 2023 |date=6 June 2023}}</ref> and was settled into the squad by [[Mathew Ryan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Maty Ryan eyeing Alessandro Circati for Buffon insight |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/ryan-rolls-out-welcome-mat-for-new-socceroo-circati/ |website=KEEPUP |language=en-AU |date=11 June 2023}}</ref> However, Circati was an unused substitute in two friendlies with the Socceroos, sitting on the bench in the matches against Argentina and [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] (on 12 September).<ref>{{cite web |title=Squad Notes: The potential debutants and returning players for Mexico clash |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/squad-notes-potential-debutants-and-returning-players-mexico-clash |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=12 September 2023 |date=1 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Socceroos play out hard-fought Mexico draw |url=https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/socceroos-play-out-hard-fought-mexico-draw |publisher=Football Australia |access-date=12 September 2023 |date=12 September 2023}}</ref>

Circati made his debut on 18 October 2023 in a [[Soccer Ashes]] [[Exhibition game|friendly]] match against [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] at [[Brentford Community Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Australia v New Zealand |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/match/australia-v-new-zealand-friendlies-18-10-2023/22278549 |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=18 October 2023 |language=en |date=18 October 2023}}</ref> He played a part in the opening goal scored by [[Harry Souttar]] and kept a [[Shutout|clean sheet]] in the process as Australia won 2–0 over [[Australia–New Zealand soccer rivalry|their rivals]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gibson |first1=Tim |title=Circati earns plaudits on Socceroos debut |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/circati-earns-plaudits-socceroos-debut |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=18 October 2023 |language=en |date=18 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Monteverde |first1=Marco |title=Alessandro Circati debuts in style for the Socceroos against New Zealand |url=https://www.news.com.au/sport/football/alessandro-circati-debuts-in-style-for-the-socceroos-against-new-zealand/news-story/814b9715b693f6a587b215580bb7c465 |website=news.com.au |publisher=NCA NewsWire |access-date=18 October 2023 |date=18 October 2023}}</ref> Circati made his competitive debut on 11 June 2024 in a 5–0 win against [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Drennan |first=Jonathan |date=2024-06-11 |title=Socceroos World Cup qualifiers As It Happened: Australia cruise to 5-0 victory |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/socceroos-world-cup-qualifiers-live-australia-host-palestine-in-perth-20240611-p5jksr.html |access-date=2024-06-11 |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |language=en}}</ref>

On 9 September 2025, Circati was named in the starting lineup for the second leg of the 2025 [[Soccer Ashes]] as [[Captain (sports)|captain]], in just his 7th appearance for the Socceroos.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2025-09-09 |title=Live: Irankunda and Toure picked to start for Australia in 'Soccer Ashes' finale |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-09-09/new-zealand-vs-australia-socceroos-live-blog-soccer-ashes/105754478 |access-date=2025-09-09 |work=ABC News |language=en-AU}}</ref> In the process he became the Socceroos' fourth youngest captain and the youngest since 1981.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-10-13 |title=Circati: It's a great honour to captain the Socceroos {{!}} Socceroos |url=https://socceroos.com.au/news/circati-its-a-great-honour-captain-socceroos |access-date=2026-05-28 |website=socceroos.com.au |language=en}}</ref> Circati revealed in a press conference during the Soccer Ashes series that former Italian goalkeeper [[Gianluigi Buffon]] played a key role in helping him choose to play for Australia over Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-04 |title=Buffon inspired Circati to pick Australia over Italy |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/46152236/circati-buffon-helped-choose-socceroos-italy |access-date=2025-09-09 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

Circati scored his first international goal on 31 March 2026 against [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] during the [[2026 FIFA Series (men's matches)|2026 FIFA Series]] at the [[AAMI Park]].<ref>https://www.fifa.com/en/match-centre/match/10017/292846/292847/400021845</ref>

